CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1781686099
OL,3,CPub bookings surge by 300% for
OL,4,CEngland's World Cup kick-off
OL,6,FJames Nicandrou, associate director at
OL,7,FOpinium, said: "With millions of young
OL,8,Fadults planning to watch World Cup
OL,9,Fmatches in pubs, the tournament looks
OL,10,Flikely to provide a welcome spending
OL,11,Fboost to the economy.
OL,13,F"More widely, our research suggests
OL,14,Fpubs continue to occupy an important
OL,15,Fplace in community life, particularly
OL,16,Ffor the young and those in rural
OL,17,Fareas, as spaces where people can come
OL,18,Ftogether to share moments ` big and
OL,19,Fsmall."
OL,26,@oD@POUuD@AOU{D@GO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
