OL,3,CPub bookings surge by 300% for
OL,4,CEngland's World Cup kick-off
OL,6,FEmma McClarkin, chief executive of the
OL,7,FBritish Beer and Pub Association,
OL,8,Fsaid: "We're expecting England's first
OL,9,Fmatch to draw fans to the pub and
OL,10,Fanticipate an extra five million pints
OL,11,Fwill be pulled as we all cheer on the
OL,12,Fteam, which will be a massive boost
OL,13,Ffor the sector.
OL,15,F"The best way to enjoy the match is,
OL,16,Fand always has been, down the pub with
OL,17,Ffriends and fellow fans, and I'd
OL,18,Fencourage everyone to head to their
OL,19,Flocal to cheer on England."
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@AOU{D@[O]
